From: conda-forge <conda-forge@example.com>
Date: Mon, 07 Apr 2025 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Remove -static-libstdc++ from Python extension targets

Embedding a private libstdc++ in _cvcuda.so causes ABI hazards when the
extension is loaded alongside other C++ libraries using conda-forge's
dynamic libstdcxx. Use the conda-forge toolchain's dynamic libstdc++.
---
 python/CMakeLists.txt | 5 -----
 1 file changed, 5 deletions(-)

diff --git a/python/CMakeLists.txt b/python/CMakeLists.txt
index aaaaaaa..bbbbbbb 100644
--- a/python/CMakeLists.txt
+++ b/python/CMakeLists.txt
@@ -69,11 +69,6 @@ function(cvcuda_python_add_module)
         set(ARG_OUTPUT_NAME ${ARG_TARGET})
     endif()

-    target_link_libraries(${ARG_TARGET}
-        PRIVATE
-            -static-libstdc++
-    )
-
     # Suppress false positive GCC-12 warning in pybind11 internals
     # This warning appears during LTO, so we need to pass it to both compiler and linker
     if(CMAKE_CXX_COMPILER_ID STREQUAL "GNU")
